<dl id="n09117l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09117l">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09117l"> 117(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> usus bride capture</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;Roman Law&rdquo;: <i>Usus</i>, on the other hand, was a mode of acquiring marital <i>manus</i> by possession of the woman as wife for a certain period of time &mdash; long cohabitation. &hellip; Comparative historians with good reason trace in <mark>usus the relics of primitive bride capture</mark>. <small> <cite a>&ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo;</cite></a> <a name="EBRL1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL1"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) XXIII p. 531</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
